<subSubSection id="9CFB88A1FF90FFA4CF92FE597B78FBCF" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="D45EDB2AFF90FFA4CF92FE597B78FBCF" blockId="30.[151,1436,386,1095]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
<taxonomicName id="13E1A0A9FF90FFA4CF92FE5979D0FE6B" authorityName="Petrunkevitch" authorityYear="1910" box="[199,473,458,483]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CF92FE5979D0FE6B" box="[199,473,458,483]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadinus tuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was based on a holotype female from Poço Grande (Fazenda Poço Grande, Juquiá, São Paulo, Brazil). The description and illustration of the holotype shows a specimen of large size (longer than 
<quantity id="131976CFFF90FFA4CAD5FE7C78CDFDA3" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
) that lacks the diagnostic needle-shaped setae of 
<taxonomicName id="13E1A0A9FF90FFA4CDBEFD817B60FDA3" authorityName="Simon, 1895:" authorityYear="1052" box="[747,873,530,555]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CDBEFD817B60FDA3" box="[747,873,530,555]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, indicating that this species does not belong to the genus. The analysis of the photos of the holotype (
<figureCitation id="4CDAC7AFFF90FFA4CD8AFDA57B66FDC7" box="[735,879,566,591]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[330,1266,1150,1961]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[330,1266,1150,1961]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 14. Epicadus pustulosus (Mello-Leitão, 1929), subadult female holotype [total length: 10.5 mm]. A–D habitus (A dorsal, B ventral, C frontal, D lateral). Photo credits: R. Pupedis and PMNH Laboratory of Arachnology crew." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458516/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Figs 14A–D</figureCitation>
), sent by the curator of the Peabody Museum of Natural History, allows us to recognize that the holotype is in fact an immature female with only the primordium of the epigynum. This species clearly belongs to a group of species that 
<bibRefCitation id="B070A6DBFF90FFA4CCE9FDED7CB5FD1F" box="[956,1212,638,663]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24408" refString="Machado, M., Teixeira, R. A. &amp; Lise, A. A. (2017) Cladistic analysis supports the monophyly of the Neotropical crab spider genus Epicadus and its senior synonymy over Tobias (Araneae: Thomisidae). Invertebrate Systematics, 31, 442 - 455. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 16074" type="journal article">
Machado 
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CB78FDEC7C61FD1F" box="[1069,1128,638,663]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
named “ 
<taxonomicName id="13E1A0A9FF90FFA4CA70FDED7D92FD1F" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[1317,1435,638,663]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pustulosus">
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CA70FDED7D92FD1F" box="[1317,1435,638,663]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">pustulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade”, which is composed of spiders with cryptic bark-dweller habitus due to its dark and rough tegument, and by the presence of large pustular setiferous tubercles in femora I and II (composed of 
<taxonomicName id="13E1A0A9FF90FFA4CB31FD557D35FD57" baseAuthorityName="Mello-LeitÃ £ o" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[1124,1340,710,735]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudatus">
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CB31FD557D35FD57" box="[1124,1340,710,735]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadus caudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Mello- 
<bibRefCitation id="B070A6DBFF90FFA4CFC2FD797939FC8B" box="[151,304,746,771]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24568" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. F. (1929) Aphantochilidas e Thomisidas do Brasil. Arquivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro, 31, 9 - 359." type="journal article">Leitão, 1929</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="13E1A0A9FF90FFA4CE1EFD797B32FC8B" authority="(Mello-Leitao, 1929)" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1929" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[331,827,746,771]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pustulosus">
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CE1EFD797A31FC8B" box="[331,568,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadus pustulosus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B070A6DBFF90FFA4CD1AFD797B3AFC8B" box="[591,819,746,771]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24568" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. F. (1929) Aphantochilidas e Thomisidas do Brasil. Arquivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro, 31, 9 - 359." type="journal article">Mello-Leitão, 1929</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="13E1A0A9FF90FFA4CCD7FD797D10FC8B" authority="Banks, 1909" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1909" box="[898,1305,746,771]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulatus">
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CCD7FD797C7BFC8B" box="[898,1138,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadus granulatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B070A6DBFF90FFA4CBD4FD797D10FC8B" box="[1153,1305,746,771]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref23652" refString="Banks, N. (1909) Arachnida from Costa Rica. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 61, 194 - 234. Benjamin, S. P. (2011) Phylogenetics and comparative morphology of crab spiders (Araneae: Dionycha, Thomisidae). Zootaxa, 3080, 1 - 108." type="journal article">Banks, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="13E1A0A9FF90FFA4CA61FD7978F5FCAF" baseAuthorityName="Mello-LeitÃ £ o" baseAuthorityYear="1929" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudatus">
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CA61FD7978F5FCAF" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadus caudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on a female holotype from the city of Rio de Janeiro, has been recorded from the state of São Paulo (
<bibRefCitation id="B070A6DBFF90FFA4CFCBFCA17999FCC3" box="[158,400,818,843]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24345" refString="Machado, M., Teixeira, R. A. &amp; Lise, A. A. (2015) Taxonomic notes on the crab spider genus Tobias Simon, 1895 (Araneae, Thomisidae, Stephanopinae). Zootaxa, 4034 (3), 565 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4034.3.8" type="journal article">
Machado 
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CE47FCA7794CFCC3" box="[274,325,818,843]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B070A6DBFF90FFA4CECBFCA17A99FCC3" box="[414,656,818,843]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24473" refString="Machado, M., Teixeira, R. A. &amp; Lise, A. A. (2018) There and back again: more on the taxonomy of the crab spiders genus Epicadus (Thomisidae: Stephanopinae). Zootaxa, 4382 (3), 501 - 530. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4382.3.4" type="journal article">
Machado 
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CD5AFCA77A4AFCC3" box="[527,579,818,843]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="13E1A0A9FF90FFA4CDF0FCA17B84FCC3" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[677,909,818,843]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pustulosus">
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CDF0FCA17B84FCC3" box="[677,909,818,843]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadus pustulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on an immature female holotype from Fonteboa, Amazonas state, northern Brazil, reaches south to the state of São Paulo (
<bibRefCitation id="B070A6DBFF90FFA4CB6BFCC57D20FCE7" box="[1086,1321,854,879]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24345" refString="Machado, M., Teixeira, R. A. &amp; Lise, A. A. (2015) Taxonomic notes on the crab spider genus Tobias Simon, 1895 (Araneae, Thomisidae, Stephanopinae). Zootaxa, 4034 (3), 565 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4034.3.8" type="journal article">
Machado 
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CBFAFCC47CE9FCE7" box="[1199,1248,854,879]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B070A6DBFF90FFA4CA61FCC5791BFC1B" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24473" refString="Machado, M., Teixeira, R. A. &amp; Lise, A. A. (2018) There and back again: more on the taxonomy of the crab spiders genus Epicadus (Thomisidae: Stephanopinae). Zootaxa, 4382 (3), 501 - 530. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4382.3.4" type="journal article">
Machado 
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CFC2FCEF78CEFC1B" box="[151,199,890,915]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). As stated in 
<bibRefCitation id="B070A6DBFF90FFA4CEFAFCE97AA8FC1B" box="[431,673,890,915]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24345" refString="Machado, M., Teixeira, R. A. &amp; Lise, A. A. (2015) Taxonomic notes on the crab spider genus Tobias Simon, 1895 (Araneae, Thomisidae, Stephanopinae). Zootaxa, 4034 (3), 565 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4034.3.8" type="journal article">
Machado 
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CD4BFCEF7A47FC1B" box="[542,590,890,915]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">et al</emphasis>
. (2015
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B070A6DBFF90FFA4CDF9FCE87AE1FC1B" box="[684,744,891,915]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24473" refString="Machado, M., Teixeira, R. A. &amp; Lise, A. A. (2018) There and back again: more on the taxonomy of the crab spiders genus Epicadus (Thomisidae: Stephanopinae). Zootaxa, 4382 (3), 501 - 530. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4382.3.4" type="journal article">2018</bibRefCitation>
), the difference in color of the pustular setiferous tubercles on the femora I and II allows an easy differentiation between 
<taxonomicName id="13E1A0A9FF90FFA4CC00FC0D7C26FC3F" baseAuthorityName="Mello-LeitÃ £ o" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[853,1071,926,951]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudatus">
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CC00FC0D7C26FC3F" box="[853,1071,926,951]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadus caudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(orange/reddish) and 
<taxonomicName id="13E1A0A9FF90FFA4CA61FC0D7904FC53" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1929" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pustulosus">
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CA61FC0D7904FC53" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadus pustulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(yellowish). The large, yellowish setiferous tubercles in the femora I and II, and also the tarsi I and II lighter than most leg articles of the holotype indicate that 
<taxonomicName id="13E1A0A9FF90FFA4CC73FC757D28FC77" authority="Petrunkevitch, 1910" authorityName="Petrunkevitch" authorityYear="1910" box="[806,1313,998,1023]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CC73FC757C3EFC77" box="[806,1079,998,1023]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadinus tuberculatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B070A6DBFF90FFA4CB6BFC757D28FC77" box="[1086,1313,998,1023]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24767" refString="Petrunkevitch, A. (1910) Some new or little known American Spiders. Annals of the New York Academy of Science, 19, 205 - 224. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1749 - 6632.1909. tb 56918. x" type="journal article">Petrunkevitch, 1910</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is a senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="13E1A0A9FF90FFA4CE70FB997B08FBAB" authority="Mello-Leitao, 1929" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1929" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[293,769,1034,1059]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pustulosus" status="syn. nov.">
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CE70FB997A02FBAB" box="[293,523,1034,1059]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadus pustulosus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B070A6DBFF90FFA4CD4EFB997AF0FBAB" box="[539,761,1034,1059]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24568" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. F. (1929) Aphantochilidas e Thomisidas do Brasil. Arquivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro, 31, 9 - 359." type="journal article">Mello-Leitão, 1929</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="FDA6BA43FF90FFA4CC5FFB997B7BFBAB" box="[778,882,1034,1059]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CC5FFB997B7BFBAB" bold="true" box="[778,882,1034,1059]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">syn. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
As Petrunkevich´s species has priority, the valid name is 
<taxonomicName id="13E1A0A9FF90FFA4CFA1FBBD7AE0FBCF" authority="(Petrunkevicth, 1910)" authorityName="Prado &amp; Baptista &amp; Machado" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Petrunkevicth" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[244,745,1070,1095]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="E6950738FF90FFA4CFA1FBBD79E7FBCF" box="[244,494,1070,1095]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadus tuberculatus</emphasis>
(Petrunkevicth, 1910)
</taxonomicName>
